Ms. Jessica Tuchman MathewsCarnegie Endowment for International PeaceWashington, DCIn present position since 1997. Previously held governmental posts that included deputy to the undersecretary of state for Global Affairs and director of the National Security Council's Office of Global Issues. Also served as a senior fellow at the Council on Foreign Relations and was founding VP and director of research of the World Resources Institute. Formerly was a member of the editorial board of the Washington Post.2006 Fourth QuarterAdded to: Hanesbrands Inc. - Winston-Salem, NCHanesbrands manufactures and markets branded apparel products. Revenues are $5 billion.
    














 















 








 



