Jessica Tuchman Mathews
Jessica Tuchman Mathews has been president of the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace, a foreign policy think tank in Washington, D.C., since 1997. She has held jobs in the executive and legislative branches of government, management and research in nonprofits, and journalism. Wikipedia*
On the C-SPAN Networks:Jessica Tuchman Mathews has 54 videos in the C-SPAN Video Library; the first appearance was a 1988 House Committee as a Vice President for the World Resources Institute. The year with the most videos was 2004 with six videos as a President for the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace. The year with the highest average number of views per program was 2012 with an average of 813 views per program. Most appearances with Joseph Cirincione (5), Madeleine K. Albright (3), Paul D. Wolfowitz (3). Most common tags: Nuclear, Foreign Policy, Iraq War (03/19/03-05/01/03.
