How Will Leadership Shuffle Affect National Security Policy?
April 28, 2011 at 5:29 PM EDT 


564842360023600Will Leadership Shuffle Shift National Security Policy?President Obama officially announced leadership changes to his national security team. Jim Lehrer discusses the staff shuffle and its policy implications with the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace's Jessica Tuchman Mathews, former CIA Acting Director John McLaughlin and former Army Vice Chief of Staff Gen. Jack Keane.2011-04-28 20:02:00disabled1901735294Ew-4ywWyazI222744222752http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/schiff-trump-wants-appoint-malleable-attorney-general-russia-investigation/Schiff: Trump wants more malleable attorney generalJared Kushner faced another round of questions about his contacts with Russian officials during and after the Trump campaign. William Brangham speaks with Rep. Adam Schiff, D-Calif, one of the lawmakers who questioned Kushner in the closed session, about whether Kushner’s answers were satisfactory and the possibility of Attorney General Jeff Sessions being forced to resign.2017-07-25 06:00 pmhttp://d3i6fh83elv35t.cloudfront.net/newshour/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/RTX3CVS4-320x196.jpg3003142530_jPdsUUPiJ4222741222748http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/attack-president-attorney-general-sessions-still-advancing-conservative-agenda/Why is Trump attacking his attorney general?President Trump's escalating criticism of Jeff Sessions over his rescual from the Russia investigation has exposed a rare public rift between a president and his attorney general, leading some to believe that Sessions may be forced out. How did we get here, and how are fellow Republicans responding? John Yang and Sari Horwitz of The Washington Post join Jeffery Brown to discuss.2017-07-25 06:00 pmhttp://d3i6fh83elv35t.cloudfront.net/newshour/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/RTX3397R-320x196.jpg30031420093xnaeNN9Kow222740222747http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/will-mccains-speech-inspire-bipartisanship-health-care-debate/Will McCain's speech inspire bipartisanship on health care?Sen. John McCain made a dramatic return to the Senate floor in his first public appearance since being diagnosed with brain cancer, calling on colleagues to change the tone and behavior of Congress to work together. Sen. Jon Tester, D-Mont., joins Judy Woodruff to discuss the high-stakes health care vote carried out by Republicans, and what he sees for the battle over the Affordable Care Act.2017-07-25 06:00 pmhttp://d3i6fh83elv35t.cloudfront.net/newshour/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/RTX3CVYH-320x196.jpg3003141885OFia3dWgaoI President Obama officially announced leadership changes to his national security team. Jim Lehrer discusses the staff shuffle and its policy implications with the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace's Jessica Tuchman Mathews, former CIA Acting Director John McLaughlin and former Army Vice Chief of Staff Gen. Jack Keane.
